NAME
    insert - create new records

SYNOPSIS
    insert <path> [field=value ...]
    echo '<json>' | insert <path>

DESCRIPTION
    Creates new records in the specified model. Records can be created
    by specifying field=value pairs on the command line, or by piping
    JSON data to stdin.

    Path can be relative (uses current directory) or absolute.
    The path should point to a model directory (e.g., /api/data/users).

OPTIONS
    field=value
        Set a field value. Can be repeated for multiple fields.
        Values are parsed as JSON if they look like JSON, otherwise
        treated as strings.

EXAMPLES
    insert /api/data/users name="John Doe" access=user
        Create a user with inline field values

    insert users email=test@example.com
        Create in relative path

    echo '[{"name":"Bob"}]' | insert /api/data/users
        Create from JSON array via stdin

    cat data.json | insert products
        Bulk insert from file

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success
    1   Error (path not found, validation failed, etc.)

SEE ALSO
    update, delete, select, describe
